postings.body: Nicknamed "Skyline Chalet," this beautiful 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom deluxe home features spectacular views of the surrounding forests and mountains and is just 10 minutes from world-class ski resorts, such as Heavenly Mountain and Sierra-at-Tahoe. This home features wood paneling throughout and has a very rustic, mountain lodge feel to it. At 2,600 square feet, the home has a very big living area that connects to the kitchen and dining area, creating a big communal space that is perfect for large gatherings. The living area features a beautiful gas fireplace and some cozy chairs to settle in to after a long day on the slopes. The custom kitchen is stocked with top-of-the-line cutlery and is perfect for preparing dinners for lots of people. The living area also includes a big-screen TV and floor-to-ceiling windows that look out on the deck and the amazing forest and mountains beyond. The spacious and cozy bedrooms in this home feature the wood paneling as well, and have a very comfortable, log cabin vibe. The master bedroom even has wood-beam ceilings and a sliding-glass door that leads straight out to the deck. It`s the perfect room for any couple in your group that wants a little privacy, from the private bathroom to the private deck area. The biggest bathroom in the house features a big, Jacuzzi-style tub as well as a spacious walk-in shower. And even the bathrooms have big windows that look out onto the gorgeous wilderness that surrounds you. This big house can sleep 10 people, has dining space for 10, and includes a private hot tub, Internet access, a steam shower, and a game room with a pool table. This game room also has a sliding-glass door that leads out to the hot tub on the deck. So late at night, you and your friends can alternate between the cozy hot tub and shooting some pool just 5 feet away. Additional amenities in this home include a gas BBQ, laundry facilities, 2 gas fireplaces, a dishwasher, and many other modern amenities.  The lower level of this home has its own separate kitchen as well, so if you want to split the levels of this home between families, it`s very easy to do so. This second kitchen also provides a bit of extra privacy for anyone who would want it. Additionally, the home has a children`s play room in the rear of the house equipped with a wrap-around couch and a crafting table with board games.  The big deck in the back of the house has spectacular views of the forest directly around you and the gorgeous mountains in the distance. There`s a picnic table on the deck, so it`s perfect for eating meals in the summertime. It`s also a great place to relax with a cocktail, read a good book, or simply catch some sun. The spacious hot tub is also out on the deck. So as you`re soaking your worn-out body after a hard day on the slopes or out hiking, you`ll be able to star gaze, look out at the trees, and wonder at the wilderness around you.  If you`re looking for a gorgeous home that offers amazing indoor spaces and outdoor spaces alike, then look no further than this beauty that sits up on a hill and overlooks the amazing countryside that is Lake Tahoe.
